    "Description": "Package updates are available for Anolis 8 that fix the following vulnerabilities:\n\nCVE-2021-27218:\nAn issue was discovered in GNOME GLib before 2.66.7 and 2.67.x before 2.67.4. If g_byte_array_new_take() was called with a buffer of 4GB or more on a 64-bit platform, the length would be truncated modulo 2**32, causing unintended length truncation.",
    "Advisory": {
      "Severity": "Moderate",
      "Issued": {
        "Date": "2021-08-25"
      },
      "Updated": {
